      "num": 1,
      "text": "What fundamentally differentiates a fraud examiner's work from that of a conventional auditor?",
      "tag": "CFE vs Auditor",
      "options": [
        "A. Review of internal controls and operational processes",
        "B. Performance of routine compliance testing",
        "C. Conducting targeted investigations based on specific allegations",
        "D. Annual assessment of financial statements"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "While auditors perform periodic and systematic reviews, fraud examiners conduct specific, targeted investigations based on allegations or indicators of irregularities. (CFE Fraud Examiners Manual 2024)",
      "justification_wrong": "Review of controls, compliance testing, and financial statement assessment are typical audit activities, not exclusive to fraud examination.",
      "difficulty": "STANDARD",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "fraud_investigation/quiz_002_en.json"
    },
    {
      "question": "During the audit of Maple Manufacturing Ltd., you discover that management has implemented a new inventory tracking system but failed to document the design of internal controls or perform any assessment of control effectiveness. When you raise this concern, the CFO states that documenting controls is the auditor's job and that management's only responsibility is to prepare accurate financial statements. \n\nRequired:\nDiscuss management's responsibilities regarding internal controls over financial reporting and explain what actions management should have taken.",
      "topic": "S3D04 - Management & Auditors Responsibilities",
      "subject": "Audit",
      "label": "Management Responsibilities for Internal Controls",
      "num": 2
    },
    {
      "question": "FinTech Solutions Inc. is a rapidly growing software company that recently went public. The board of directors is composed primarily of the founder's family members and long-time friends, with only one independent director. The company's audit committee consists of three board members, none of whom have accounting or financial expertise. During the year, the CFO resigned abruptly, and the controller has been acting in both roles for the past six months. The company has experienced significant turnover in its finance department. As the external auditor, you are concerned about the governance structure and its impact on your audit.\n\nRequired:\nDiscuss management's responsibilities regarding corporate governance and internal control, and explain how weaknesses in these areas affect your responsibilities as an auditor. What actions should you take in response to the governance concerns identified?",
      "topic": "S3D04",
      "metadata": {
        "lo": "Management & Auditors Responsibilities",
        "bloom": "analysis",
        "difficulty": "medium"
      },
      "num": 3
    },
    {
      "question": "XYZ Corporation's management has requested that the external auditors assist in preparing the company's financial statements and also provide recommendations on improving internal controls over financial reporting. The auditors have agreed to both requests. Discuss the responsibilities of management versus the auditors in the financial statement preparation process and evaluate whether the auditors' agreement to assist with both tasks is appropriate under professional standards.",
      "topic": "S3D04",
      "subtopic": "Management & Auditors Responsibilities",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "bloom": "analyze",
      "num": 4
    },
    {
      "question": "As the external auditor of Maple Manufacturing Ltd., you have discovered that management failed to implement adequate controls over inventory counts despite your prior year management letter recommendation. The CFO has indicated they do not plan to address this deficiency due to cost constraints. What are your professional responsibilities in this situation, and what actions should you take?",
      "required_response": [
        "Assess whether the control deficiency represents a significant deficiency or material weakness that must be communicated to those charged with governance",
        "Communicate the matter in writing to the audit committee or board of directors, including the potential impact on the financial statements",
        "Consider whether management's refusal to address the deficiency affects the auditor's risk assessment and planned audit procedures",
        "Evaluate if additional substantive procedures are required to obtain sufficient appropriate audit evidence over inventory",
        "Assess whether the limitation represents a scope limitation that could impact the audit opinion",
        "Document management's response and the auditor's consideration of the matter in the audit file",
        "Consider whether this raises concerns about management integrity that affect the auditor-client relationship"
      ],
      "topic": "S3D04",
      "subject": "Audit",
      "type": "Communication of Control Deficiencies",
      "num": 5
    },
