      "question": "During the audit planning phase, the engagement partner is discussing the respective responsibilities for fraud detection with the new CFO of a public company client. The CFO states: 'Since you auditors are the experts in detecting fraud and you're examining our financial statements in detail, I expect your audit will uncover any fraud that exists in our organization.' \n\nRequired:\nExplain the auditor's responsibilities regarding fraud detection in a financial statement audit and clarify any misconceptions in the CFO's statement.",
